.\" Man page for {{ project_name }}
.\" Contact: {{ author_email | default("support@example.com") }}
.TH {{ project_slug | upper }} 1 "2026-01-01" "{{ project_name }}" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
{{ project_slug }} \- {{ description }}
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B {{ project_slug }}
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIINPUT\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
{{ description }}

This tool processes files and stdin inputs with support for glob patterns, dry-run mode, and comprehensive configuration management.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\--config\fR \fIFILE\fR
Config file (default is $HOME/.config/{{ project_slug }}/config.yaml)
.TP
\fB\--json\fR
Output results as JSON
.TP
\fB\-q, \--quiet\fR
Suppress all output except errors
.TP
\fB\-v, \--verbose\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB\--debug\fR
Enable debug logging with stack traces
.TP
\fB\--color\fR=\fImode\fR
Color output: auto, always, never
.TP
\fB\--install\fR
Install shell completions and initialize config
.TP
\fB\--uninstall\fR
Remove shell completions and config files
.TP
\fB\--man\fR
Generate and display man page
.TP
\fB\--dry-run\fR
Preview changes without executing them
.TP
\fB\-f, \--force\fR
Bypass confirmation prompts for destructive operations
.TP
\fB\--usage\fR
Show usage information
.SH EXAMPLES
Process a single file:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{{ project_slug }} file.txt
.EE
.RE
.PP
Process files matching a glob pattern:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{{ project_slug }} "**/*.txt"
.EE
.RE
.PP
Process stdin:
.PP
.RS
.EX
cat file.txt | {{ project_slug }} -
.EE
.RE
.PP
Install shell completions:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{{ project_slug }} --install
.EE
.RE
.PP
Preview changes without executing:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{{ project_slug }} --dry-run file.txt
.EE
.RE
.SH CONFIGURATION
The tool uses a configuration file located at:
.PP
$HOME/.config/{{ project_slug }}/config.yaml
.PP
Configuration precedence (highest to lowest):
.RS
.IP 1.
Command-line flags
.IP 2.
Environment variables (prefixed with {{ project_slug | upper | replace('-', '_') }}_)
.IP 3.
Config file
.IP 4.
Hardcoded defaults
.RE
.SH COMPLETION
Shell completion scripts are installed via the \fB\--install\fR flag and support bash, zsh, and fish.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred
.SH SEE ALSO
The full documentation is available at: {{ project_url | default("https://github.com/example/" + project_slug) }}
.SH AUTHOR
{{ author_name | default("Developer") }} <{{ author_email | default("support@example.com") }}>
